This is an heirloom airgun that you'll pass along to your grandchildren and beyond. The gun's heft and balance convey quality and substance. It fills your hand without feeling bulky or oversized. Unlike many modern air pistols, the P1 isn't made of molded synthetics. It's a solid metal gun with finely checkered walnut grips. And, it's truly ambidextrous. The 11mm dovetails make it easy to mount a pistol scope or a red dot sight. This .177 version of the P1 has two power levels. Low power is approx. 380 fps, and high or full power is 600 fps. The different power levels are created by cocking the gun to different lock points. The distance you shoot, the weight of the pellet and the type of target will determine which power level is best. title: For Sale/Trade:  Mint Condition Ruger Mark III 22/45 Target  .22 LR de-lawyered blued
postcontent:
For sale is a mint-condition Ruger Mark III 22/45 Target Model .22 LR semi-auto in blued finish. Factory rail and UTG Red Dot sight. It has been upgraded for fast, flawless magazine changes and easier takedown (in other words, it's been “de-Lawyered” and breaks down exactly as if were a Mark II model). The mags fall right into your hand (like they OUGHT to!) when you push the release. 

Appearance and function on this gun are immaculate.  After mods (see below) were made and sight was attached, approximately 150 rounds were fired at the local range to “zero in” the firearm and make everything functioned perfectly. It does. In typical Ruger fashion, it “eats” anything you put in the magazine. CCI, Federal, Winchester, you name it. NEVER Remington. Just don't...

All internal friction points were burnished and polished for a silky trigger pull, including the square block where the barrel/receiver meets the frame. No mallets or tools necessary to break this gun apart.

Sight is UTG “red/green” dot variable intensity.  Keep both eyes open, bring the weapon up, and put the dot where you want it. Exhale. Pull the trigger. Bullseye. Simple as that.

Auction includes firearm, 2 magazines, speed loader, genuine Ruger Mounting rail, scope (as pictured) and hard padded gun case

Background checks on gun purchases amount to de facto gun registration. UNIVERSAL background checks on gun purchases amount to de facto UNIVERSAL gun registration. 

The default "lawyered-up" (the ones that won't release your mags and are difficult to break down) versions of the 22/45s are selling in the  $300 – $400 price range. Hard to put a value on my day-and-a-half with 600 grit sandpaper, polishing compound and gunsmithing tools pulling out all the garbage like gutting a fish, but mag changes and the trigger pull are are nicer than other 22/45s by a long shot... 

Cost of the sight was moderate. If you don't want it, I'll take $40 off the price.  Mounting rail stays on the gun.

The fact that this sale will take place between two consenting adults without paperwork is priceless. Make me an offer. I will also consider trades. .22 lr ammo mostly.

title: For Sale/Trade:  IMMACULATE 1954 High-Standard Dura-Matic .22 lr semi-auto
postcontent:
For sale/trade is an immaculate manufactured in 1954 High Standard Dura-Matic .22 lr semi-auto pistol. This gun is in “as-new” condition both functionally and cosmetically. Bluing pristine, without marks, and grips/handles are in absolutely perfect condition with no wear visible. 

This model has “threaded” barrel-removal system (see picture), which is superior to the “push-button” models because it does NOT have any springs to wear out over time and it functions as well after 1,000 take downs as it does when new. It also has a locking side button on the thumbwheel that keeps the threaded retention wheel absolutely tight while shooting. 

It has the famous High Standard “loaded chamber” indicator on the rear of the slide. The safety on the rear of the frame also functions as the slide lock. Mag release is located left forward, above the trigger guard. Handles both standard and high-velocity .22 lr ammo. Not recommended for hyper-velocity rounds, such as Stingers. People shoot 'em in HS pistols, but I've never fired any in THIS weapon.

This gun is SOLID metal. It is pure joy to hold, shoot, and handle.

Firearm has no visible nicks, scratches, rust or other signs of wear inside or out. 

Two genuine High Standard magazine are included (one blued and one stainless), and both have been “tuned” to accept either CCI or Federal ammo (does not care for Remington cartridges, however).

I will include the carbon-steel magazine adjustment tool along with instructions so that the new owner may custom “fine tune” the mags for any desired ammo.

This firearm has absolutely NO issues. Everything about this gun, inside and out, is 100%. The trigger pull is smooth and crisp, and sights are “on the money” for 25 – 50 yards.

Auction includes firearm, 2 magazines, speed loader, mag adjustment tool and padded gun case.

I also have the Owner's manual in electronic form, which I will email the buyer.

As a High Standard in this condition with 2 factory magazines is almost impossible to find, I'd like to entertain serious cash offers in the $550 range. I would also consider partial trade for .22 lr or other ammo.
